<doc id="1237391" wikidata="Q5021626" url="?curid=1237391" title="Call login system">
<text>A call login system is a service for telephone equipment that handles staff logons, often in call centers. In such environments, logging on is usually required in order to make or receive calls. The system also helps in calculating work hours and break timings. Examples of providers include AVAYA and Nortel.

