<doc id="1237412" wikidata="Q172307" url="?curid=1237412" title="Guy Tunmer">
<text>Percival Guy Tunmer (1 December 1948 – 22 June 1999) was a racing driver from South Africa. He participated in one Formula One World Championship Grand Prix, his home race in 1975, driving a Lotus 72 for a local team, Team Gunston. He finished 11th, scoring no championship points. He later found success in Formula Atlantic.

Guy Tunmer was killed in a motorcycle accident in his native South Africa in 1999.

